This paper is about developing a chatbot using deep learning models for financial investment customer service. The paper discusses the use of BERT models for intent recognition and uncertainty measure, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also discusses the usage of BERT as a language model for automatic spelling correction, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also mentions the usage of mixed-integer programming for optimizing decision thresholds, which falls under cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
